en_297163_0	The Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi (SFHQ-KLN) with the objective of improving sports talents of troops in Kilinochchi launched a cricket and volleyball tournament and finals were held on Wednesday (9) January.
en_297163_1	The cricket tournament gave the win to cricketers of the 21 Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) team, organized under the supervision of the 65 Division.
en_297163_2	11 Gajaba Regiment (GR) cricketers got the runner-up slot.
en_297163_3	3 GR volleyball players of the 57 Division won the championship in the volleyball tournament, organized by the 57 Division with the help of 3 GR troops.
en_297163_4	1 GR became the runner-up.
en_297163_5	In the meantime, two civil teams from Mankulam Maha Vidyalaya and Karanchi Sports Club vied for supremacy in volleyball during the same tournament.
en_297163_6	After a close tussle Karanchi Sports Club volleyball players won the championship.
en_297163_7	Brigadier Deepthi Jayathilake, General Officer Commanding, 66 Division, attended as the Chief Guest in the awarding ceremony and gave away trophies to the winners in cricket while Brigadier Wasantha Kumarpperuma, General Officer Commanding, 65 Division distributed trophies and certificates to the winners in volleyball.
en_297163_8	Brigade Commanders, Commanding Officers, Senior Officers, Other Ranks and school students watched the finals.
